Documentation.name: SAF
Documentation.notes: System Architecture Framework (SAF) is an architecture framework to define architectures for complex cyber-physical systems. The profile implements the SAF concept model defined by INCOSE (GfSE as German Chapter) and provides useful SysML-based stereotypes, diagram types and linking rules.

select distinct sc.name as "System Capability", sc.note as "Notes", oc.name as "Enabling Operational Capability", uc.name as "Supporting System Use Case", sp.name as "Supported By System Process", req.name as "Refined by System Requirement" from ((((((((t_object sc left join t_connector oc_enabling on sc.object_ID = oc_enabling.start_object_id and oc_enabling.stereotype = 'SAF_SystemCapabilityEnabling') left join t_object oc on oc_enabling.end_object_id = oc.object_id and oc.stereotype = "SAF_OperationalCapability") left join t_connector uc_supporting on sc.object_ID = uc_supporting.start_object_ID and uc_supporting.stereotype = "SAF_SystemCapabilitySupport") left join t_object uc on uc_supporting.end_object_id = uc.object_id and uc.stereotype = "SAF_SystemUseCase") left join t_connector supporting_sp on sc.object_ID = supporting_sp.end_object_id and supporting_sp.stereotype = "SAF_SystemProcessEnabling") left join t_object sp on supporting_sp.start_object_id = sp.object_id and sp.stereotype = "SAF_SystemProcess") left join t_connector refining_req on sc.object_id = refining_req.end_object_id and refining_req.stereotype = "SAF_SystemRequirementRefinement") left join t_object req on refining_req.start_object_id = req.object_id and req.stereotype = "SAF_SystemRequirement") where sc.stereotype = "SAF_SystemCapability"

select distinct id.value as "ID", sreq.stereotype as "Requirement Stereotype", sreq.name as "System Requirement", sreq.note as "Notes", src.stereotype as "Source Stereotype", src.name as "Source" from ((t_object sreq left join t_connector req_src on sreq.object_id = req_src.start_object_id and (req_src.stereotype = "SAF_SystemRequirementRefinement" or req_src.stereotype = "SAF_SystemRequirementDerivation" or req_src.stereotype = "SAF_SystemRequirementFunctionalRefinement" or "SAF_SystemFunctionalRequirementConstraint" )) left join t_object src on req_src.end_object_id = src.object_id and (src.stereotype = "SAF_SystemUseCase" or src.stereotype = "SAF_SystemCapability" or src.stereotype = "ProxyPort" or src.stereotype = "SAF_StakeholderRequirement" or src.stereotype = "SAF_SystemRequirement" or src.stereotype = "SAF_SystemNonFunctionalRequirement" or src.stereotype = "SAF_SystemFunctionalRequirement")) left join t_objectproperties id on (sreq.object_id = id.object_id) where (sreq.stereotype = "SAF_SystemRequirement" or sreq.stereotype = "SAF_SystemNonFunctionalRequirement" or sreq.stereotype = "SAF_SystemFunctionalRequirement") and id.Property in ('id')

select distinct op.name as "Operational Process", op.note as "Notes", os.name as "Refining Operational Story", oc.name as "Enabling Operational Capability", operf.name as "Process Performed by" from ((((((t_object op left join t_connector os_refining on op.object_ID = os_refining.start_object_ID and os_refining.stereotype = "SAF_OperationalProcessRefinement") left join t_object os on os_refining.end_object_id = os.object_id and os.stereotype = "SAF_OperationalStory") left join t_connector op_enabling on op.object_ID = op_enabling.start_object_ID and op_enabling.stereotype = "SAF_OperationalProcessEnabling") left join t_object oc on op_enabling.end_object_id = oc.object_id and oc.stereotype = "SAF_OperationalCapability") left join t_object ap on op.object_ID = ap.parentID and ap.Object_Type = "ActivityPartition") left join t_object operf on ap.Classifier = operf.object_id and operf.stereotype = "SAF_OperationalPerformer") where op.stereotype = "SAF_OperationalProcess"

select distinct oc.name as "Operational Capability", oc.note as "Notes", os.name as "Supporting Operational Story", op.name as "Exhibiting Operational Performer", req.name as "Refined by Stakeholder Requirement" from ((((((t_object oc left join t_connector os_supporting on oc.object_ID = os_supporting.start_object_ID and os_supporting.stereotype = "SAF_OperationalCapabilitySupport") left join t_object os on os_supporting.end_object_id = os.object_id and os.stereotype = "SAF_OperationalStory") left join t_connector op_exhibit on oc.object_ID = op_exhibit.end_object_ID and op_exhibit.stereotype = "SAF_OperationalPerformerExhibit") left join t_object op on op_exhibit.start_object_id = op.object_id and op.stereotype = "SAF_OperationalPerformer") left join t_connector req_refinement on oc.object_ID = req_refinement.end_object_ID and req_refinement.stereotype = "SAF_StakeholderRequirementRefinement") left join t_object req on req_refinement.start_object_id = req.object_id and req.stereotype = "SAF_StakeholderRequirement") where oc.stereotype = "SAF_OperationalCapability"
